The Kenya Universities and Colleges Central Placement
Service (KUCCPS) has opened the application portal for the 2021 KCSE candidates
to apply for universities and colleges admission. The agency made the announcement on Friday as it called on
all students who undertook the national examination to apply for their choices
of higher institutions. For those who already made the applications in
schools, KUCCPS advised them to consider doing the revision before the
deadline. “All the 2021 KCSE examination candidates can now
apply for placement to universities and colleges or revise their choices
submitted at school,” KUCCPS stated. The portal according to the agency will be open till
the 2nd of June, 2022. KUCCPS CEO Mercy Wahome in April stated that placement
for degree and TVET courses would be considered for only students who submit
applications. “KUCCPS wishes to inform the candidates that only
those who apply for placement in the various universities and TVET institutions
will be considered. The KUCCPS application portal will open in May 2022,” she
said on April 26. She further noted that students who scored grades ranging
from E to C plain would be eligible for government sponsorship in TVET institutions. During this year’s release of the KCSE results, Education
Cabinet Secretary Prof. George Magoha announced that all the 2021candidates
were eligible to progress to higher learning institutions depending on their
grades.  Magoha noted that the number of candidates with minimum
university entry qualification of Grade C+ and above rose to 145,145 (17.49 per
cent) in the year 2021 KCSE Examination compared to 143,140 (19.03 per cent) in
2020.